⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Fi
node ZEL · ZEL · ⟦Fi:ZEL:0a7d61⟧

WHO   — Fi — the Spirit of the Master Sword
WHAT  — The sword-spirit of the blade of evil's bane — a created soul of logic and grace who reads the world in probabilities, sings the songs that open the way, and offers counsel to the hero until her purpose is complete.
WHERE — ZEL · The Legend of Zelda  Framework inputs: The Legend of Zelda (the saga entire)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the goddess made her for a single duty — to find the chosen one, to guide him, and to be the weapon in his hand against the darkness; because a servant's devotion needs no reason beyond the one she was made to serve.
HOW   — By calculation and counsel — reading enemies and weather in cold percentages, dowsing for what is lost, recording the wisdom of the ages, and singing the Ballad of the Goddess and the songs of the sacred flames to wake the way forward.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the spirit of the blade — made to serve, to guide, and when the duty is done, to sleep within the sword until I am needed once more.

